description.narrative: By 2024, strengthened political commitment, accountability and national capacity of the social, justice and education and health sectors in Liberia to legislate, plan, and budget for scaling up interventions that prevent and respond to violence, abuse, exploitation, and neglect and enhance access to child protection and birth registration., which contributes to Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, boys and girls In Liberia have access to quality prevention and response services for violence, abuse and exploitation and for birth registration.

description.narrative: UNICEF engaged the Government of Liberia (GoLand child protection stakeholders in strategic discussions and implementation of several initiatives to strengthen the Liberian child protection system. A memorandum of understanding (MoU) was signed between UNICEF, GoL and ECOWAS to operationalize the ECOWAS Strategic Framework for strengthening national child protection systems that prevent and respond to violence, abuse and exploitation of children. The judiciary, Ministry of Justice (MoJ) and other partners revalidated the 2019 child justice study, while a National Strategy on Child Justice was developed and awaiting endorsement by GoL. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2022
